help:
Use `$PREFIXhelp command` to get specific help pages by switching out the command part
 Some pages to start with: `waifu` `husbando` `yuri` `yaoi` `fam` `tree` `remove` `breakup` `relationship` `ship` `anipic` `block`
Use `$PREFIXhelp more` for more

relationship:
Sets your relationship with the person and optionally offers them a relationship with you:
`$PREFIXrelationship @user dad -> son` Would mean that they are your dad and you are their son
`$PREFIXrelationship @user waifu` Would just set them as your waifu
The `$PREFIXrelationship dad -> son @user` format also works
ship:
Ship two users!
`$PREFIXship @user1 @user2 bro -> sis` or maybe `$PREFIXship @user1 daughter -> @user2 mom`
It needs two mentions, and the type of the relationship with an arrow inside: ->
Note: things like mom -> dad would mean that one is the mom of dad and vice versa, it doesn't make sense
anipic:
`$PREFIXanipic` to get a random pic with your fam
`$PREFIXanipic @user1 @user2 ...` to explicitly specify who you want on the pic
`$PREFIXanipic picname` to specify which image to draw, you can check $PREFIXlistanipic or the name of a generated file for the name
The combination of the above two commands also works
Use $PREFIXuploadanipic to upload image bases ($PREFIXhelp uploadanipic)
$PREFIXanipicuploader to check who uploaded the base
listanipic: Lists all of the pic names
uploadanipic:
`$PREFIXuploadanipic name (optional)` with the file attached
There are two main ways you can upload an image base:
-The image by itself, with the markers placed in
-In layers, with the layers being image files in ascending name order
Markers: These are rectangles with a few rules
-Must be filled with the color #202225
-Must not be rotated
-Must be at least 20px per side
-Must NOT overlap with eachother
You might want to use pngs to retain the sharpness of the markers
About the layers:
-Their names must be sortable, for example layer1 layer2 layer3 (latter ones get on top) (A B C also works)
-If there are three layers, the second one will be scanned for markers and **discarded!**
-If there are two layers, the first layer will be used and it is kept
Recognized image formats: png, jpg, jpeg, jfif, webp, gif (not animated)
The image files need to be under 10MiB and 2000px per side
If your upload is erroneous or you find one that is undesirable please say so on the support server
This command might become premium-only in the future
anipicuploader: `$PREFIXanipicuploader picname` to see who uploaded the base for that pic
block:
`$PREFIXblock @user (or user ID)` silently blocks the user so they won't be able to register a relationship with you
Use the commands $PREFIXunblock $PREFIXlistblockeds and $PREFIXclearblockeds along with it
listblockeds: Lists the users you have blocked
